cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.PL

The paper deals with analyzing performance interferences faced by queries due to concurrent query executions in a shared cluster computing environment. This involves understanding resource contentions and workload management in the cluster. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with analyzing query performance, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper proposes a new system and metrics for analyzing query interactions, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with attributing blame for contentions, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with task placement strategies, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
